  "body": "This lets callers of Sabre routing (`swap_map_trial`) inject the type of analysis they want performing, at compile time.  This in turn lets Sabre layout avoid storing the full rebuild information during its forwards-backwards passes, when all it actually cares about is the swap counting and final layout (and really, it doesn't even care about the swap counting, but that's effectively free).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nBuilt on top of #14912.\r\n\r\nOn the HWB12 benchmark we recently merged to `main`, this PR (on top of #14912) shows a modest (~2-3%) performance improvement in `SabreLayout`, which isn't a _huge_ amount, but it isn't nothing.",
  "created_at": "2026-03-12T16:13:08Z",
